sentences: Dame Julie Bethridge Topp  (born 14 May 1958), known as Jools Topp, is one half of the Topp Twins, a music comedy duo from New Zealand; the other member is her twin sister Lynda Topp.
The sisters were both appointed Dames Companion of the New Zealand Order of Merit in the 2018 Queen's Birthday Honours.
Jools Topp and her twin sister Lynda were born on 14 May in 1958 in Huntly, to Jean and Peter, and grew up on a dairy farm in Waikato.
Topp attended Ruawaro Combined School during the 1960s and early 1970s.
After leaving school in 1976, Jools and Lynda Topp joined the New Zealand Territorial Force and were posted at the Burnham Military Camp near Christchurch for six weeks.

Much of their life has been in the public eye and their mother was interviewed by Radio New Zealand about the closure of the New Zealand Woman's Weekly magazine in 2020 talking about how much her daughters had been featured in these magazines.
Jools Topp was diagnosed with breast cancer in October 2006 at the age of 48.

Jools Topp has been singing and entertaining with her sister for decades, touring live music and comedy performances as well as performing in TV and film.

Jools Topp and her twin sister Lynda were born on 14 May in 1958 in Huntly, to Jean and Peter, and grew up on a dairy farm in Waikato.
Topp attended Ruawaro Combined School during the 1960s and early 1970s.
The twins have been singing together since they were five years old and their brother gave them a guitar when they were 11.
After leaving school in 1976, Jools and Lynda Topp joined the New Zealand Territorial Force and were posted at the Burnham Military Camp near Christchurch for six weeks.

Much of their life has been in the public eye and their mother was interviewed by Radio New Zealand about the closure of the New Zealand Woman's Weekly magazine in 2020 talking about how much her daughters had been featured in these magazines.
Jools Topp is a skilled horsewoman and for many years had a 6.9 hectares (17 acres) property in Helensville, north of Auckland, with her partner.
